Coronavirus travel health
Check the latest information on risk from COVID-19 for Namibia on the TravelHealthPro website
See the TravelHealthPro website for further advice on travel abroad and reducing spread of respiratory viruses during the COVID-19 pandemic.
You should contact local authorities for information on testing facilities.
International travel
Hosea Kutako International airport is open and flights are operating normally. Check with your travel company for the latest information.
Other countries may restrict movement or bring in new quarantine rules with little warning. You should check the travel advice for the countries on your route for the latest information.
Entry and borders
See Entry requirements to find out what you will need to do when you arrive in Namibia.
Be prepared for your plans to change
No travel is risk-free during COVID-19. Countries may further restrict travel or bring in new rules at short notice, for example due to a new COVID-19 variant. Check with your travel company or airline for any transport changes which may delay your journey home.
If you test positive for COVID-19, you may need to stay where you are until you test negative. You may also need to seek treatment there.
Plan ahead and make sure you:
can access money
understand what your insurance will cover
can make arrangements to extend your stay and be away for longer than planned
Travel in Namibia
The Government of Namibia is no longer providing statistics on COVID-19 case numbers.
All COVID-19 restrictions have been removed. Voluntary compliance to public health and social measures is encouraged.
